    "Html": "Could you be a little more specific about what the problem is.  When you say the &quot;Single Click Editing&quot; solution doesn't work, what doesn't work about it?  The event isn't called?  Is what you're looking for just to attached to the click event on a cell?  If so, you cannot use MouseLeftButtonDown as that is captured by DataGridCell.cs.  You can use PreviewMouseLeftButtonDown or MouseDoubleClick.  You can also work around it by using a DataGridTemplateColumn and attach a Click event on a custom element that you create.\r\n",
